<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 716/96 of 19 April 1996 adopting exceptional support measures for the beef market in the United Kingdom </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 716/96, veiselihaturu erakorraliste toetusmeetmete kasutuselev&otilde;tu kohta &Uuml;hendkuningriigis </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> 19. aprill 1996 EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 805/68 of 27 June 1968 on the common organization of the market in beef and veal (1), as last amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No 2417/95 (2) and, in particular, Article 23 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 805/68 veise- ja vasikalihaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, viimati muudetud komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2417/95, eriti selle artiklit 23, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Decision 96/239/EC of 27 March 1996 on emergency measures to protect against bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) (3) prohibits the exportation of live bovine animals, or any part of them, from the United Kingdom to other Member States and their export to third countries as a result of the incidence of BSE in the United Kingdom; whereas the United Kingdom has prohibited the introduction of bovine animals of more than 30 months at the time of slaughter into the human food and animal feed chains; whereas these measures involve serious disturbances in the market of the United Kingdom; whereas it is therefore necessary to take exceptional measures to support this market; whereas it is appropriate to establish a Community co-financed scheme authorizing the United Kingdom to purchase the animals covered by the abovementioned prohibition with a view to killing and subsequently destroying them; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: komisjoni 27. m&auml;rtsi 1996. aasta otsusega 96/239/E&Uuml; h&auml;dakaitsemeetmete kohta veiste spongioosse entsefalopaatia (BSE) vastu keelatakse BSE esinemise t&otilde;ttu &Uuml;hendkuningriigis elusveiste v&otilde;i nende mis tahes osade eksport &Uuml;hendkuningriigist teistesse liikmesriikidesse ja kolmandatesse riikidesse; &Uuml;hendkuningriik on keelanud tapmisajal &uuml;le 30 kuu vanuste veiste kasutamise inimeste ja loomade toiduahelas; nimetatud meetmetega seonduvad t&otilde;sised h&auml;ired &Uuml;hendkuningriigi turul; seet&otilde;ttu on vaja selle turu toetamiseks v&otilde;tta erakorralisi meetmeid; on kohane luua &uuml;henduse kaasrahastatav kava, millega &Uuml;hendkuningriigis lubatakse eespool nimetatud keeluga h&otilde;lmatud loomi kokku osta nende tapmiseks ja j&auml;rgnevaks h&auml;vitamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of the extent of the disease, in particular, of its probable duration, and consequently of the magnitude of the efforts needed to support the market, it would be appropriate for such efforts to be shared by the Community and the United Kingdom; </inglise>
<eesti> t&otilde;ve ulatust ja eelk&otilde;ige selle t&otilde;en&auml;olist kestust ning selle t&otilde;ttu turu toetamiseks vajalike j&otilde;upingutuste suurust silmas pidades oleks kohane jagada need j&otilde;upingutused &uuml;henduse ja &Uuml;hendkuningriigi vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in most cases animals slaughtered above the age of 30 months are cull cows; whereas the most recently observed price of carcases of cows on the United Kingdom market was equivalent to ECU 1 per kilogram live weight and that it is therefore appropriate to base the purchase price on this, without prejudice to the possibility of subsequent adjustment in the light of developments; whereas, in similar cases the Community has contributed to the overall expenditure incurred at a rate of 70 %; whereas a price of ECU 1 per kilogram is equal on average to a price of ECU 560 per animal; whereas it is appropriate, in view of the large numbers of animals concerned and in the interests of simplification, to provide a Community contribution of ECU 392 per animal; </inglise>
<eesti> suurem osa &uuml;le 30 kuu vanuselt tapetavatest loomadest on praaklehmad; lehmar&uuml;mpade viimane vaadeldud hind &Uuml;hendkuningriigi turul oli 1 ek&uuml;&uuml; eluskaalu kilogrammi kohta ning seet&otilde;ttu on kohane v&otilde;tta see ostuhinna aluseks, v&auml;listamata v&otilde;imalust seda hiljem vastavalt turu arengule kohandada; &uuml;hendus on samasugustel juhtudel katnud kogukuludest 70%; hind 1 ek&uuml;&uuml; kilogrammi kohta teeb looma keskmiseks hinnaks 560 ek&uuml;&uuml;d; asjaomaste loomade suurt arvu arvestades ja lihtsustamise huvides on kohane s&auml;testada &uuml;henduse toetuseks 392 ek&uuml;&uuml;d looma kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, it is necessary to ensure that the animals concerned are killed and destroyed in a manner which does not pose any threat to human health or the health of other animals; whereas, it is therefore necessary to specify the conditions for the destruction of these animals and of the controls to be carried out by the United Kingdom authorities; whereas, so as to avoid that animals to be slaughtered under this scheme mix with animals not covered by this scheme and that mistakes as to identity occur, they should be kept separately in the lairage to a slaughterhouse, as well as in the slaughterhouse itself; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja tagada, et asjaomased loomad tapetaks ja h&auml;vitataks inimeste v&otilde;i teiste loomade tervisele ohutul viisil; seet&otilde;ttu on vaja kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata nimetatud loomade h&auml;vitamise ja &Uuml;hendkuningriigi asutuste poolse kontrolli tingimused; v&auml;ltimaks k&auml;esoleva kava alusel tapetavate loomade segunemist k&auml;esoleva kavaga h&otilde;lmamata loomadega ning vigu loomade identifitseerimisel, tuleks neid tapamaja lautades ja ka tapamajas hoida eraldi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, provision should be made for Commission experts to check compliance with the conditions as specified; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks s&auml;testada komisjoni ekspertide v&otilde;imalus kontrollida nimetatud tingimuste t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Management Committee for Beef and Veal has not delivered an opinion within the time limit set by its chairman, </inglise>
<eesti> veise- ja vasikalihaturu korralduskomitee pole oma esimehe m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul arvamust esitanud, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The United Kingdom competent authority shall be authorized to purchase any bovine animal aged more than 30 months which does not show any clinical sign of BSE, presented to it by any producer or his agent, which was, during a period of at least three months prior to its sale, present on a holding located on the territory of the United Kingdom. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriigi p&auml;deval asutusel lubatakse osta iga mis tahes tootja v&otilde;i tootja esindaja pakutavat iga &uuml;le 30 kuu vanust veist, kellel ei ilmne BSE kliinilisi tunnuseid ja kes on enne m&uuml;&uuml;ki v&auml;hemalt kolm kuud olnud &Uuml;hendkuningriigi territooriumil asuvas p&otilde;llumajandusettev&otilde;ttes. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The animals referred to in paragraph 1 shall be killed in specially designated slaughterhouses, the heads, internal organs and carcases shall be permanently stained. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 viidatud veised tapetakse spetsiaalselt selleks etten&auml;htud tapamajades ja nende pead, siseelundid ja r&uuml;mbad m&auml;rgistatakse h&auml;vimatu v&auml;rviga. </eesti>
<inglise> The stained material shall be transported in sealed containers to specially authorized incineration or rendering plants, where it shall be processed and then destroyed. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;rgistatud materjal transporditakse pitseeritud konteinerites eriloa saanud tuhastamis- v&otilde;i j&auml;&auml;tmetehastesse, kus see t&ouml;&ouml;deldakse ja seej&auml;rel h&auml;vitatakse. </eesti>
<inglise> No part of the abovementioned animals may enter into the human food or animal feed chains or be used for cosmetic or pharmaceutical products. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski eespool nimetatud veise osa ei tohi sattuda inimeste v&otilde;i loomade toiduahelasse, samuti ei tohi neid kasutada kosmeetika- v&otilde;i farmaatsiatoodetes. </eesti>
<inglise> A representative of the United Kingdom competent authority shall be permanently present in the slaughterhouse referred to above in order to supervise the operations in question. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriigi p&auml;deva asutuse esindaja viibib alaliselt eespool nimetatud tapamajas, et k&otilde;nealust toimingut kontrollida. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding the first subparagraph, the United Kingdom competent authority may allow the on-farm slaughter of an animal where existing animal welfare practice would require this. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimesest l&otilde;igust olenemata v&otilde;ib &Uuml;hendkuningriigi p&auml;dev asutus lubada veist tappa p&otilde;llumajandusettev&otilde;ttes, kui seda n&otilde;uab sel ajal kehtiv loomakaitsetava. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding the second subparagraph, the hides of the animals referred to in paragraph 1 do not have to be stained or destroyed provided that they have been treated in such a way that they can only be used for leather production. </inglise>
<eesti> Teisest l&otilde;igust olenemata ei pea v&auml;rvima ega h&auml;vitama l&otilde;ikes 1 viidatud loomade nahku, kui need on t&ouml;&ouml;deldud viisil, mis laseb neid kasutada &uuml;ksnes nahatoodete valmistamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The slaughterhouses referred to in paragraph 2 shall be organized and operated in such a way as to ensure that: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 2 viidatud tapamaju korraldatakse ja k&auml;itatakse viisil, mis tagab, et: </eesti>
<inglise> - no bovine animal, the product from the slaughter of which is intended for human or animal consumption, is present in the slaughterhouse when animals are being slaughtered under this scheme, </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;kski veis, kelle tapasaadused on m&otilde;eldud inimestele v&otilde;i loomadele tarbimiseks, ei oleks tapamajas ajal, kui loomi tapetakse vastavalt k&auml;esolevale kavale; </eesti>
<inglise> - where it is necessary for bovine animals to be slaughtered under the scheme to be held in lairage, they shall be kept separate from bovine animals which it is intended to slaughter for human or animal consumption, and </inglise>
<eesti> - kui k&auml;esoleva kava kohaselt tapetavaid veiseid on vaja hoida laudas, hoitakse neid eraldi veistest, keda kavatsetakse tappa inimestele v&otilde;i loomadele tarbimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> - where it is necessary for products derived from animals slaughtered under this scheme to be stored, such storage shall be separate from any storage facility used for meat or other products destined for human or animal consumption. </inglise>
<eesti> - kui k&auml;esoleva kava kohaselt tapetud veiste tapasaadusi on vaja ladustada, asub ladu eraldi k&otilde;igist hoiuruumidest, mida kasutatakse inimestele v&otilde;i loomadele tarbimiseks m&otilde;eldud liha v&otilde;i muude toodete hoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The United Kingdom competent authority shall: </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriigi p&auml;dev asutus: </eesti>
<inglise> - carry out the necessary administrative checks and effective on-the-spot supervision of the operations referred to in paragraphs 2 and 3, and </inglise>
<eesti> - teeb vajalikud halduskontrollid ning l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 viidatud toimingute kohapealse kontrolli ja </eesti>
<inglise> - control those operations on the basis of frequent and unannounced inspections, in particular to verify that all stained material has been effectively destroyed; </inglise>
<eesti> - kontrollib nimetatud toiminguid sageli ja ette teatamata, veendumaks eelk&otilde;ige, et kogu v&auml;rviga m&auml;rgistatud materjal on tegelikult h&auml;vitatud. </eesti>
<inglise> The results of these checks and controls shall be made available to the Commission on request. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud kontrollide ja j&auml;relevalve tulemused tehakse taotluse korral k&auml;ttesaadavaks komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> If the number of animals presented for sale and subsequent destruction exceeds the number for which there is capacity to destroy in the United Kingdom, the competent authority may limit access to this scheme. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ostmiseks ja hilisemaks h&auml;vitamiseks pakutavate loomade arv on suurem, kui &Uuml;hendkuningriigil on v&otilde;imalik h&auml;vitada, v&otilde;ib p&auml;dev asutus k&auml;esolevas kavas osalemist piirata. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The price to be paid to producers or their agents by the United Kingdom competent authority under Article 1 (1) shall be ECU 1 per kilogram live weight. </inglise>
<eesti> Tootjatele v&otilde;i nende esindajatele &Uuml;hendkuningriigi p&auml;deva asutuse poolt artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel makstav hind on 1 ek&uuml;&uuml; eluskaalu kilogrammi eest. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community shall co-finance the expenditure incurred by the United Kingdom for the purchases referred to under Article 1 (1) at a rate of ECU 392 per purchased animal which has been destroyed in accordance with the provisions of Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendus kaasrahastab &Uuml;hendkuningriigi poolt seoses artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 viidatud ostudega kantud kulud 392 ek&uuml;&uuml; ulatuses iga ostetud looma kohta, mis on h&auml;vitatud koosk&otilde;las artikli 1 s&auml;tetega. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The conversion rate to be applied shall be the agricultural rate valid on the first day of the month of the purchase of the animal in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Kohaldatav &uuml;mberarvestuskurss on k&otilde;nealuse looma ostmise kuu esimesel p&auml;eval kehtiv p&otilde;llumajanduslik &uuml;mberarvestuskurss. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The United Kingdom shall adopt all measures necessary to ensure proper application of this scheme and full compliance with the provisions of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriik v&otilde;tab k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed, et tagada k&auml;esoleva kava n&otilde;uetekohane rakendamine ning k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tete t&auml;ielik t&auml;itmine. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall inform the Commission as soon as possible of the measures which it has taken and of any amendments thereto. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriik teavitab komisjoni v&otilde;etud meetmetest ja neis tehtud muudatustest esimesel v&otilde;imalusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The United Kingdom competent authority: </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendkuningriigi p&auml;dev asutus: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) shall inform the Commission each Wednesday, of the number of animals: - purchased, and </inglise>
<eesti> a) teatab komisjonile igal kolmap&auml;eval nende loomade arvu, kes eelneva n&auml;dala jooksul on k&auml;esoleva kava kohaselt </eesti>
<inglise> - slaughtered </inglise>
<eesti> - ostetud ja </eesti>
<inglise> under this scheme during the previous week; </inglise>
<eesti> - tapetud; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) shall establish a detailed report of the controls which they have taken under the measures referred to in Article 3 and shall communicate this to the Commission each quarter. </inglise>
<eesti> b) koostab &uuml;ksikasjaliku aruande artiklis 3 viidatud meetmete alusel tehtud kontrollidest ja edastab selle kord kvartalis komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to Article 9 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 (4), Commission experts, accompanied where appropriate by experts from the Member States, shall carry out, in collaboration with the United Kingdom competent authority, on-the-spot checks to verify compliance with all the provisions of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artikli 9 kohaldamist, teevad komisjoni eksperdid koost&ouml;&ouml;s &Uuml;hendkuningriigi p&auml;deva asutusega ja vajadusel koos liikmesriikide ekspertidega kohapealseid kontrolle, et veenduda k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse k&otilde;igi s&auml;tete t&auml;itmises. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> The measures taken under this Regulation shall be considered to be intervention measures within the meaning of Article 1 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel v&otilde;etud meetmeid k&auml;sitletakse sekkumismeetmetena m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 2 t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
